                    "body": "Switching to binary downloads worked for a few days. But since earlier today, that fails too.\r\n\r\n* installing *source* package \u2018arrow\u2019 ...\r\n** package \u2018arrow\u2019 successfully unpacked and MD5 sums checked\r\n** using staged installation\r\n*** Using centos-8 binary for rhel-8\r\n*** No C++ binaries found for centos-8\r\n*** Successfully retrieved C++ source\r\n*** Building C++ libraries\r\n**** cmake\r\n**** arrow  \r\n\r\nThe installation continues seemingly successful, but subsequent tests that try to load arrow fail.\r\n\r\nAbout two hours ago, the corresponding log output was:\r\n\r\n* installing *source* package \u2018arrow\u2019 ...\r\n** package \u2018arrow\u2019 successfully unpacked and MD5 sums checked\r\n** using staged installation\r\n*** Using centos-8 binary for rhel-8\r\n*** Successfully retrieved C++ binaries for centos-8\r\n**** Binary package requires libcurl and openssl\r\n**** If installation fails, retry after installing those system requirements\r\n\r\n",
