                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Roland Weber",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
                    },
                    "body": "The download logic in the Arrow package on CRAN refers to bintray.\r\nhttps://github.com/apache/arrow/blob/maint-3.0.x/r/tools/linuxlibs.R#L22\r\n\r\nbintray says it's shutting down and will disable all accounts this Saturday, May 1st.\r\nhttps://bintray.com/\r\n\r\n??Attention: All Bintray services will be deprecated and your accounts will be disabled on May 1st 2021.??\r\n\r\nI guess I'll be looking for an installation path that does not require any downloads beyond the actual CRAN package. Could it be that the download problems are because bintray is serving warning pages with the shutdown notice?\r\n\r\nOh... I just noticed that I install first the Arrow package from CRAN, then pyarrow from PyPI. If I reverse the installation order, maybe the CRAN package picks up the binary from the pyarrow wheel.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rolweber",
