                        },
                        "displayName": "Neal Richardson",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
                    },
                    "body": "CRAN releases don't download Arrow source from bintray, that's for nightly builds and for C++ binaries, so that's why sometimes a C++ binary was found and sometimes not. In any case, the upcoming 4.0 release (coming this week) eliminates all bintray. \r\n\r\nIn your first error log, it looks like Arrow C++ source downloaded but untar failed. That likely means that you got a bad response from an Apache mirror. I would expect that to succeed on retry.",
